  <refnamediv>
    <refname>RPI_serialGetchar</refname>
    <refpurpose>Function to get next character from serial device</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   RPI_serialGetchar(fd)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>fd:</term>
      <listitem><para> file-descriptor obtained from RPI_serialOpen function</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
This function returns the next character available on the serial device. This call will block for up to 10 seconds if no data is available (when it will return -1).
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

